MOBO Awards
The MOBO Awards (an acronym for &quot;Music of Black Origin&quot;) were established in 1996 by Kanya King. They are held annually in the United Kingdom to recognize artists of any race or nationality performing music of black origin. 50 Cent has received three awards.
